“Colourful Progression of Buildings” by @futureofarchitecture 🇷🇺 .
.
Viewers are requested to join me in congratulating Kirill @futureofarchitecture for this delightful progression of colourful buildings in Moscow, comprising the Salaryevo Park residential complex by PIK group 🎈🎉🎈.
.
Kirill is a Moscow based photographer sharing his vision of modern architecture in Russia, on IG, predominantly around Moscow.
.
Apart from his excellent gallery, what’s particularly unique about Kirill’s feed is he shares architectural and building location details with his audience in English. Any photographers who are planning trips to Moscow are therefore particularly recommended to view Kirill’s gallery, @futureofarchitecture, they will not be disappointed.
.

node.text:
I may travel far and wide but I always go back to where I feel the most at home - the desert.

@columbiasportswear_me

I guess we need the other seasons to realize how special this one is. It’s such a weird time always. I find so much happiness looking at the beauty of the mood. The changing colors. Yet there’s such a feeling of melancholy too, such a sadness, knowing how fleeting it is, how soon the trees full of color will be barren. But if that isn’t one of the most important thought processes to come out of a day, to put towards life, I don’t how else to process it. Thankful for the moments of gold, however long they last.
